o cool before slicing and serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This bread is made without an oven! The result is moist and full of flavour, and the whole grains add extra nutrition. If you are not in a hurry, reduce the yeast and give the bread more time to rise, as described in the variation.<\/i>","If using a silicone bread mould, extend steaming time by <b>10 minutes.<b>","For a longer rise, the amount of fresh yeast can be halved in <b>step 4<b> allow covered bread dough to rise for <b>2-3 hours<b> in a warm place or overnight in the fridge, then continue with <b>step 5.<b><br>- <strong>Nut Bread:<\/strong> Instead of sunflower seeds, add <b>80 g nuts<b> (hazelnuts or walnuts).<br>- <strong>Carrot Bread:<\/strong> After <b>step 2,<b> place <b>100 g carrots,<b> cut in pieces, in mixing bowl and chop <b><strong>4 sec\/speed 5.<\/strong><b> Leave carrots in mixing bowl and continue with recipe.<br>- <strong>Carrot Walnut Bread:<\/strong> After <b>step 2,<b> place <b>80 g carrots,<b> cut in pieces, in mixing bowl and chop <b><strong>4 sec\/speed 5.<\/strong><b> Leave carrots in mixing bowl and continue with recipe. In <b>step 4<b> replace the <b>100 g sunflower<b> seeds with <b>30 g walnuts<b>."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h","20 slices"]}